[ ] -l: Long format, displaying detailed information.
[ ] -a: Include entries starting with a dot (hidden files).
[ ] -R: Recursive listing of subdirectories.
[ ] -h: Human-readable file sizes (e.g., KB, MB, GB).
[ ] -t: Sort by modification time, newest first.
[ ] -S: Sort by file size.
[ ] -r: Reverse the order of the sort.
[ ] -g: Similar to -l, but exclude owner information.
[ ] -1: Force output to be one entry per line.
[ ] -i: Display the inode number of each file.
[ ] -G: Enable colorized output.
[ ] -U: Do not sort; list entries in directory order.
[ ] -d: List directories themselves, not their contents.
[ ] -F: Append indicator (one of /=@|) to entries.
[ ] -c: Use time of last change instead of last modification.
[ ]-u: Use time of last access instead of last modification.
[ ] -q: Force printing of non-graphic characters in file names as the character ?.
[ ] -A: List all entries except for . and ...
[ ] --color: Enable colorized output (alternative to -G).

